            <offset>0</offset>
            <sentence>
                <offset>0</offset>
                <text>An 8-y-old boy, who was the second child of non consanguineous parents, was referred for evaluation of short stature noticed since 5 y of age.</text>
                <annotation id="1">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0004322</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="103"/>
                    <text>short stature</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>143</offset>
                <text>He was normal at birth except for sparse hair.</text>
                <annotation id="2">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0008070</infon>
                    <location length="11" offset="34"/>
                    <text>sparse hair</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>190</offset>
                <text>He had normal development and his scholastic performance was good.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>257</offset>
                <text>He did not have any symptoms of immunodeficiency and malabsorption.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>325</offset>
                <text>His parents were of normal height.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>360</offset>
                <text>On clinical examination, his weight was 20.7 kg (3rd centile for age), height 99 cm (less than 3rd centile for age), upper segment (US): lower segment (LS) ratio 1.2:1 (infantile), and arm span 109 cm which was greater than his height.</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>596</offset>
                <text>He also had a mild scoliosis to left and brachydactyly with 5th digit clinodactyly, bilaterally.</text>
                <annotation id="3">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0002650</infon>
                    <location length="9" offset="19"/>
                    <text>scoliosis</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="4">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0001156</infon>
                    <location length="13" offset="41"/>
                    <text>brachydactyly</text>
                </annotation>
                <annotation id="5">
                    <infon key="type">webanno.custom.Phenotypes</infon>
                    <infon key="HPOterm">http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_0004209</infon>
                    <location length="22" offset="60"/>
                    <text>5th digit clinodactyly</text>
                </annotation>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>693</offset>
                <text>He had sparse and light colored hair, eyebrows and eyelashes.</text>
