            <sentence>
                <offset>755</offset>
                <text>His blood counts, serum alkaline phosphatase (215 U/dl) and immunoglobulin profile were normal (IgG 1660 mg/dl, IgE 343 IU/ml, IgM 81.2 mg/dl and Ig A 303 mg/dl).</text>
            </sentence>
            <sentence>
                <offset>918</offset>
                <text>His radiographs revealed, widened metaphysis with irregularities and brachydactyly (Fig. 1) As the features were suggestive of cartilage hair hypoplasia, sequencing of RMRP gene was done and a homozygous g. 70 A &gt; G mutation was identified.</text>
